<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Instance on PIGSTY</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/</link><description>Recent content in Instance on PIGSTY</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>PGSQL Instance</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-instance/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-instance/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main dashboard for a single PGSQL instance: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-instance"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Instance is the main dashboard for a single PostgreSQL instance, providing comprehensive instance-level metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-instance"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-instance.webp" alt="pgsql-instance"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGRDS Instance</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgrds-instance/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgrds-instance/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RDS version of PGSQL Instance: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgrds-instance"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGRDS Instance is the RDS version of PGSQL Instance, focusing on PostgreSQL-native metrics without host-level metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgrds-instance"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgrds-instance.webp" alt="pgrds-instance"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGCAT Instance</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgcat-instance/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgcat-instance/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instance info from database catalog: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgcat-instance"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGCAT Instance shows instance-level information retrieved directly from PostgreSQL system catalog.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgcat-instance"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgcat-instance.webp" alt="pgcat-instance"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Persist</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-persist/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-persist/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Persistence metrics for PGSQL instance: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-persist"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Persist focuses on persistence-related metrics: WAL generation, XID consumption, checkpoints, archiving, and I/O patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-persist"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-persist.webp" alt="pgsql-persist"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Proxy</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-proxy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-proxy/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Detailed metrics for HAProxy: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-proxy"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Proxy shows detailed metrics for a single HAProxy load balancer instance serving PostgreSQL traffic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-proxy"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-proxy.webp" alt="pgsql-proxy"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Pgbouncer</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-pgbouncer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-pgbouncer/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Metrics overview for Pgbouncer: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-pgbouncer"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Pgbouncer shows connection pooling metrics for a single Pgbouncer instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-pgbouncer"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-pgbouncer.webp" alt="pgsql-pgbouncer"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Session</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-session/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-session/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Session and active/idle time metrics: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-session"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Session focuses on session statistics and active/idle time distribution for a single PostgreSQL instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-session"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-session.webp" alt="pgsql-session"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Xacts</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-xacts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-xacts/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Transaction, lock, TPS/QPS metrics: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-xacts"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Xacts focuses on transaction processing, lock activity, and TPS/QPS metrics for a single PostgreSQL instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-xacts"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-xacts.webp" alt="pgsql-xacts"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Exporter</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-exporter/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/instance/pgsql-exporter/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Self-monitoring metrics for exporters: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-exporter"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Exporter shows self-monitoring metrics for the Postgres exporter and Pgbouncer exporter components.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-exporter"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-exporter.webp" alt="pgsql-exporter"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>